.TH "drm_mode_legacy_fb_format" 9 "drm_mode_legacy_fb_format" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_mode_legacy_fb_format \- compute drm fourcc code from legacy description
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "uint32_t" drm_mode_legacy_fb_format
.BI "(uint32_t bpp "  ","
.BI "uint32_t depth "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bpp" 12
bits per pixels
.IP "depth" 12
bit depth per pixel
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Computes a drm fourcc pixel format code for the given \fIbpp\fP/\fIdepth\fP values.
Useful in fbdev emulation code, since that deals in those values.
